briefdescription.para: Input a list, test each item against a Boolean filter, and return a new list. Side effects (such as actions) are allowed by using Then and Else blocks.

detaileddescription.para: This type may be used as List input into expressions, and to generate side effects (actions) when iterating through a list.

The lists may be, e.g., All ListItems of a question All (un) selected ListItems of a question All repeat responses of a QF All questions at a given repeat level Sibs (all|prev|following) of the current item
To use the current item during a iteration use the variable $ITER
